Print Comparison Results

Source: R/print.R
print.tna_comparison.Rd

Print Comparison Results

Usage

# S3 method for class 'tna_comparison'
print(x, ...)

Arguments

x

A tna_comparison object.

...

Additional arguments passed to the tibble print method.

Value

x (invisibly).

See also

Model comparison functions compare(), compare.group_tna(), plot.tna_comparison(), plot_compare(), plot_compare.group_tna()

Examples

model_x <- tna(group_regulation[1:200, ])
model_y <- tna(group_regulation[1001:1200, ])
comp <- compare(model_x, model_y)
print(comp)
